Patient then felt kind of nauseated. It started when we first got on the phone. She couldn't put her finger on it. Patient went to the emergency room last Monday. The only way she would go see a doctor, is if she saw that the arm was getting much bigger, like it grew 2" more. If she had a hard time breathing, she would call 911. The patient drove slowly, when she got home, her husband was outside and she got out of the car and told him she was woozy and dizzy. She went in side and when she got to steps, she couldn't lift her foot up and had to crawl up the steps. She began violently shaking, she sat in a chair, it got worse. She is now 68 years old, she owns her own business sowing, active, walks and had no issues at all. Now, she was not able to go down stairs to sowing area and do anything. She had to use the buggy at the grocery store, because she can't walk and at night, some nights, she has a bell, her husband had to hold her from seizure like shaking it was terrifying. She had her second dose on 25Mar2021, the next day, she experienced worsening effects, she never had this shaking and not being able to function like she did before. She was concerned Ithat she was having seizure and palsy, because she had never been like this. It didn't start until after the first shot was bad and after the second one, it intensified even more. The patient stated that ever since the shot, her life had changed, she had never been in this position before. She can't think of anything else, checked her medications, never had any problems. She had been to the doctor, they can't detect anything else that could have caused her to get in this condition. Nothing like this. The patient stuttering, having to think of what she has to say, she had never ever had anything like this. She wanted to reach out because it was life changing and she was afraid and have never experienced anything like this at all. It has taken away any opportunity to get a job or anything. an episode of idiopathic thrombocytopenic purpura (ITP); bleed out; getting blisters in the mouth; Initial information received on 26-Apr-2021 regarding an unsolicited valid serious case from a consumer.  This case involves male patient (in his early 60s in 2011) who experienced an episode of idiopathic thrombocytopenic purpura (ITP) (immune thrombocytopenia), getting blisters in the mouth (oral mucosal blistering) and bleed out (haemorrhage), after receiving INFLUENZA USP TRIVAL A-B SUBVIRION NO PRESERVATIVE VACCINE [FLUZONE].  The patient's past medical history, medical treatment(s), vaccination(s) and family history were not provided.  No concomitant medication(s) were given to the patient.  In Nov-2011, the patient received a 0.5 ml dose of suspect INFLUENZA USP TRIVAL A-B SUBVIRION NO PRESERVATIVE VACCINE (lot UT473AB and expiration date not reported) via unknown route in an unknown administration site for prophylactic vaccination. The patient reported that the he only had the lot number and no other identifiers of the vaccine and that the provider told the consumer that he had a Sanofi vaccine.  In 2011, the patient developed a serious episode of idiopathic thrombocytopenic purpura (ITP) (immune thrombocytopenia) (one week latency), described as getting blisters in the mouth (oral mucosal blistering) (one week latency), had a platelet count of 1000 from 190000 the week prior and being a bleed out (haemorrhage) (one week latency). These events were assessed as medically significant. The patient was in inpatient hospitalization and reported that a week before the vaccine he had a physical and his platelet count then was 190000. The patient remained in the hospital for 4 weeks.  The patient was treated with chemotherapy to get the immune system on track, while he was in the hospital.  The patient recovered from all the reported events on an unknown date.  It was reported that he was now looking into getting the COVID-19 (coronavirus disease) vaccine but was informed that the COVID-19 vaccine should not be given if someone experienced ITP after receiving a vaccine with the same ingredients as the Covid-19 vaccine; that the consumer did not get the high dose in 2011. Reported that he does not have good site and was needing to transfer the phone to the spouse to type in a website for him. There was no more information for this report due to the consumer not having the information.; Sender's Comments: This case involves male patient who had immune thrombocytopenia, oral mucosal blistering and haemorrhage, a week after vaccination with FLUZONE. The time to onset is compatible. Platelet count of the patient was 1000 from 190000 (the week prior before the vaccination). However, patient's medical condition at the time of vaccination and lab tests ruling out alternate etiologies were not reported. Based upon the reported information, the role of a vaccine cannot be assessed.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt had immunization appt at 8:45AM. Pt was accompanied by father. Father checked in with secretary, secretary gave Father standard immunizations forms and directed father and pt into room 1. This nurse was sitting at nurses station facing secretary. At no time did father state or produce any additional shot record besides what were already on file. This nurse reviewed pt immunization record to determine what vaccines were needed and gathered VIS sheets for shots needed based on the current vaccine record on file. This nurse took the VIS sheets into room to discuss with father. This nurse informed and discussed needed and optional vaccines (Hep A). Father was educated on Hep A and asked if would like to start the 2 dose series. Father was told them that pt would come back in 6 months for second and final dose then. Father agree to all vaccines and stated he had no questions or concerns. This nurse prepared vaccines and went back into the room. At this point, this nurse provided father with 2 copies of updated shot record. Father was by pt side at time of injections. After receiving vaccines father was informed he could make follow up appt for second Hep A before leaving if desired. When leaving father said good bye and was directed up to cashier's office.  About 10:15AM mom calls in angry stating pt was given duplicate vaccines. Mom states she sent an updated shot with father for today's appt. Mom stated father came home with updated shot record from us. It was then she realized at today's appt pt received vaccines that were on the shot record from the pediatrician's office that father was to bring in. Mom states father told her he gave the shot record to the secretary. This nurse spoke with mom and was given an account of how the visit transpired. This nurse explained that this nurse was sitting at nurses station facing secretary's desk. At no time did pt's father state or produce updated shot record to the secretary or this nurse. At no time before, during, or after vaccines did father state there an additional vaccine record that existed. Nor, voiced a concern that the vaccines this nurse was giving today did not sound right. Mom states she wanted to file a complaint. This nurse notified the supervising nurse. I was working as the coordinator at on offsite vaccine event where primarily second doses of Pfizer Covid vaccine were being administered. I was pulled over by the nurse immediately following vaccination of the recipient. The nurse informed me that the recipient had provided her a consent form with Pfizer vaccine information and indicated that she was there for her second dose of Pfizer vaccine. The nurse administered the Pfizer Covid vaccine and then reviewed the vaccination record card presented by the recipient at which time she discovered that the first document a dose of Covid vaccine was Moderna. She immediately informed the recipient and the recipient did acknowledge to me that she had requested the Pfizer vaccination as her second dose because she thought that's what she had received. The recipient had received a consent form with the Pfizer lot number when she presented to the registration desk indicating that she was there to receive her second dose of Pfizer vaccine. I informed the recipient of the CDC guidance which indicates that no further doses are necessary when a mixed series of Pfizer and Moderna Covid vaccines are  administered. I suggested that she could choose to inform her healthcare provider and to certainly report any adverse effects. The recipient reported mild cramping in her left hand while we were talking to her during the post observation. And she indicated that this might have been a psycho somatic symptom. We asked the recipient to stay an additional 10 minutes beyond the 15 required minutes for observation. She reported no further issues and that the cramping in her hand had resolved. Her mother later called the health office regarding the medication error.

I received the first dose of the Pfizer/BioNTech vaccine on April 15, 2021 at 3:00PM. On April 17, 2021, I began experiencing involuntary body jerks. They initially felt like hypnogogic jerks, but I was fully awake. The body jerks primarily occur in my trunk (seldomly in my lower extremities) and are visibly noticeable. She was immediately sent to the ER where she was found to have stridor but without angioedema, hypoxia, urticaria, vomiting, hypotension, or other signs of anaphylaxis.  During her stay in the ER, I oversaw her care and her symptoms completely resolved after IM Epi, benadryl, famotidine, albuterol/iptratropium, steroids, and magnesium.  After an observation period in the ED, she had no recurrence of symptoms and was ultimately discharged.

patient was unconscious; patient was unconscious; UTI; Bedridden; Patient began to vomit; This case was received via FDA VAERS (Reference number: 0967119) on 27-Apr-2021 and was forwarded to Moderna on 27-Apr-2021.    This regulatory authority case was reported by an other health care professional (subsequently medically confirmed) and describes the occurrence of LOSS OF CONSCIOUSNESS (patient was unconscious) and SYNCOPE (patient was unconscious) in an 87-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 029L20A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below.     Concurrent medical conditions included Penicillin allergy, Syncope (granddaughter states patient has episodes of syncope) and Wheelchair user.    On 22-Jan-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 22-Jan-2021, the patient experienced LOSS OF CONSCIOUSNESS (patient was unconscious) (seriousness criterion medically significant) and SYNCOPE (patient was unconscious) (seriousness criterion medically significant). 22-Jan-2021, the patient experienced URINARY TRACT INFECTION (UTI), BEDRIDDEN (Bedridden) and VOMITING (Patient began to vomit). At the time of the report, LOSS OF CONSCIOUSNESS (patient was unconscious) and SYNCOPE (patient was unconscious) had resolved and URINARY TRACT INFECTION (UTI), BEDRIDDEN (Bedridden) and VOMITING (Patient began to vomit) outcome was unknown.        The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown.   For mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular), the reporter did not provide any causality assessments.   After administration, the patient remained in waiting area for the recommended 15 minutes observation time. Approximately 20 minutes after vaccination, patient was unconscious and appeared not to be breathing, but pulse was palpable. Pharmacist administered 1 dose of 0.3mg epinephrine via epi-pen into patient's left thigh. The patient quickly regained consciousness, spoke to family, said she did not feel well. Emergency medical services (ems) arrived. The patient began to vomit, was placed on stretcher and left with ems. A few hours later the granddaughter reported that the patient had a urinary tract infection (UTI) and physical exam by emergency room (ER) attributed her experience to untreated infection.; Sender's Comments: Based on the information provided which includes a strong temporal association between the use of mRNA-1273 vaccine and onset of the reported events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. At the time of the report, SEIZURE (thinks it was a potential seizure), PRESYNCOPE (vasovagal effect from the needle), MUSCULOSKELETAL STIFFNESS (Patient fell off the bench onto the floor and became rigid and stiff and exhibited some rigid movement) and FALL (Patient fell off the bench onto the floor and became rigid and stiff and exhibited some rigid movement) was resolving.        The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Unknown) was unknown.   For mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Unknown), the reporter did not provide any causality assessments.   Concomitant medications taken by the patient were not provided.  The reporter reported that patient never had any allergic reactions to vaccines or medications before and had no past medical histories for vasovagal reactions. After receiving the vaccine, the patient waited in the pharmacy for 15 minutes - 20 minutes. The patient fell off the bench onto the floor and became rigid and stiff and exhibited some rigid movement. The patient was out of it for 15-30 seconds. The reporter stated that she called 911. The patient came to, his eyes were huge, but he was aware to self and surroundings. The emergency team came, took the patient's vitals which were stable and stated the patient likely experienced a vasovagal effect from the needle. However, the reporter thinks it was a potential seizure; more than a vasovagal response. Emergency team offered no treatment. The emergency team had encouraged the patient to follow up with a doctor but the patient did not want to make a big scene.  Emergency team offered no treatment for the patient. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Effects of vaccine were all normal during the first few days and through the first week.  Had a bit of heart palpitations and fever after dose #2 - but it subsided by day 2 and i was back to normal mostly, no real issues.  A week later i experienced an episode of almost-syncope in which i start falling forward in my seat and almost hit the wall in front of me and couldn't hold my head up.  This has NEVER happened to me before.  I did have a panic attack AFTER this because of how scared i had become of that feeling, but i recognize that and know the difference.  After that i continued to experience bouts of dizziness and disequilibrium.  I have almost fallen reaching for things, opening my car door, walking, etc.  Several weeks later i experienced another flare up of the syncope feeling while at work where i almost fainted again and was able to regain composure and the disequilibrium sensation lasted for several days to which i sought medical help.  I have been visiting a chiropractor and a physical therapist for over a month now with minor improvement.  I still experience unexplained episodes that prevent me from being able to work properly or leave my home as it would be unsafe to drive or be out in case i need medical assistance.  I have never experienced ANYTHING like this until i was vaccinated and three months later it is still affecting my quality of life.
LAB_DATA: Blood work on 2/17/2021 and then again on March 10th. X-rays on 4/5/2021

I had the vaccination (my second) and waited the required 15 minutes after the injection.  I felt fine and got on my bike and road home.  I took a longer route (10 miles), and I remember things up to almost the end.  The bike ride ended with a bad fall, I presumably had a syncopal event and crashed my bicycle.  Bad hit on helmet, and I was unconscious for probably five minutes.  I was found and woken up by a passerby (I have no memory of this) and then the EMTs arrived.  Checked into Emergency Room.  They suspected a cardiac event, but I have so far passed all the tests (exercise stress test, echocardiogram, normal QT).  I have *never* had an event like this, the bike ride, while a little long, was quite normal for me.  I also note that I had possibly not had enough to eat or drink that morning.  So, based on the curious timing of this event, I personally believe it's related to the shot.  I also don't really believe this is an anxiety related syncopal event (it was more than an hour after the shot), but rather I suspect an immune response, perhaps aggravated by dehydration/lack of enough food.  But who knows?  I was out cold, and don't remember the minute or so up to the crash.  I did go back to inspect the bikeway that I was on to see if there was anything there that could have caused a crash (tree branches, rough surface) and I found nothing.  It was a pretty flat easy bike path at that point.
LAB_DATA: Many, many ekgs over May 1-> May 3 (normal) Exercise stress test May 3.  Very good. Echocardiogram May 5.  Normal

I had a patient come in at 10:05am for a Moderna Covid vaccine. Just before 11am we received a call from the patient's roommate that the patient arrived home and collapsed, it was also mentioned her blood pressure was high. We explained that they needed to call 911 but the patient did not want to go to the hospital. We explained that this patient must go to the hospital and get evaluated. They did end up calling 911.  Approximately 45 minutes later I received another call from the patient's roommate that EMS did not believe this was a reaction from the vaccine. The roommate mentioned that she was in fact mistaken about the blood pressure and it was actually low (92/54 mmHg). She also mentioned that the patient was vomiting.   Around 1:45pm I received a call from the roommate to tell me that the patient had died.

2nd shot administered 4/21 and a couple of days later (4/23-4/24) I experienced headache, nausea, chills and feeling hot (but no fever) fatigue and vomiting. I could not eat much (basically soup). The vomiting went went away but the other symptoms lasted 2 days, then I was okay.  A week later (4/29-4/30) I experienced severe traveling pain. It was an immediate onset of  pain that started ~2:00PM with a headache, then it radiated to the back of my neck, then back of both of my shoulders, then my back, while pain extended from my shoulders down my arms (primarily my left arm) down to my fingertips, then down both my legs to my feet and toes. It was very severe pain and it was so sudden and intense. I took 15mg Meloxicam for the pain (1 every 2 hours, then about every 4 hours) for the rest of the day and throughout the evening. I experienced chills and I was very hot but my temperature was only 98.1.  The pain gradually went away and I have not experienced that level of pain since.  I could only think that this was a side affect of the vaccine. I reported it to my Primary Care Physician this morning during our scheduled visit and she encouraged me to report this to site. She acknowledges that it may not be related to the Moderna vaccine, but that it was important that it be reported in case other people experience the same thing and it will allow trending analysis to occur.

A mild headache, chills, and bodyaches began on 5/1. It worsened the following day. It was on the left frontal and maxillary sinus regions and left occipital region. Mild left knee itching, redness, and warmth began. On 5/5, skin is hypersensitive. Maculopapular rash began on left ventral aspect of hand and resolved with application of hydrocortisone 1% cream. Bilateral arms also began itching and resolved on its own. Bilateral knee itching, redness, and warmth and hindfoot itching comes and goes. I began noticing bilateral cheek redness and warmth (flushed) that continues today on 5/6.

At around 9 pm I felt a funny feeling in my lips that made me feel like I might have trouble talking.  It didn't last long, but my daughter suggested I take my blood pressure.  It registered 177/90 something.  Thought that was unusually high considering we had just been sitting talking for hours after my shot, no exertion at all.  I felt good. We waited 15-20 minutes to check in again.  No nervousness or anything.  It had climbed into the 190/100 range.  My daughter suggested we go to the ER.  I didn't think it necessary.  After maybe 20 minutes we took it again and it was just over 200/low 100 something.  My daughter said sorry Mom but this is getting very high we are going to ER.  We got there near 11:30 pm I believe.  When we arrived my blood pressure registered 220/116.  Doctors thought I hadn't taken my blood pressure medication. (wrong, I always take it)  Doctors thought I was nervous about the shot.  (wrong, it had been a very calm afternoon and evening with my adult daughter who is a health care provider.  Tests came back fine.  They had me stay for a little bit but then sent me home with instructions to see my Cardiologist the following week because they felt maybe my blood pressure meds were no longer adequate.  I don't think they believed that extremely hight BP was from the vaccination, but I absolutely do.  I saw my Cardiologist on Monday. He felt all was fine.  Adjusted the dosage on one blood pressure med but did believe the high BP could have been from vaccination.  On Sunday May 14 I took it easy.  My BP came down slowly by increments of 10 for the systolic throughout the day.  By Monday I was at 140/90 at home.
LAB_DATA: Had an EKG, Urinalysis, Blood work

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I tracked my symptoms in a notebook because they were so severe on Day 1. Day 1-3: sore arm, headache, dizziness, shortness of breath, foggy brain, unable to focus, chills/uncontrollable shaking for several hours, body aches. Day 4: Same symptoms as above but milder. Bleeding gums when brushing teeth on left side of mouth (this NEVER happens). Painful gums (does happen when very sick with a virus). Day 5-6: Feeling better, but tired. Day 7: Tired, headache, nausea following exercise. Day 8-12: Mild feeling of discomfort while peeing. Tired every day.  A bitt foggy every day but this happens with pollen season. Day 18: tired, trouble breathing on treadmill- I attributed this to pollen as it went away the next day when I closed the window. Day 20 (May 1): While out with friends, after having lunch and a glass of wine, I jumbled a few words and could not say them correctly. There were just about two words in two sentences. I tried a few times and they kept coming out wrong. It was nothing I have ever experienced before. We laughed it off but I felt very unsettled and a bit concerned about driving home. I drove home and was fine. I remain tired and feeling foggy which could be  due to pollen. I have scheduled an appointment with a clinician today and hope to have some blood work done.
OTHER_MEDS: Multivitamin, vitamin C, magnesium and calcium,

I am a very active, healthy 42 year old female. After the first shot it took me until April 25th before I felt 100% better (2 weeks and 3 days). My symptoms for the first and second are in alignment, however, they have been even more intense for the second. I am miserable. I am thankful I have a strong support system. I am suffering. Every night I have weird nightmares and am "water tortured" where I wake feeling as though a gallon of water has been dumped on me as my "phantom fevers" break. They break through the day as well but not as often. I have been taking my temperature around the clock as my biggest complaint is my head. I feel as though I have a high fever but I actually haven't had a fever even once. My head has an awful manufactured feeling and makes me feel ichy. I have done little else than lay horizontal in bed or on the couch. Last week I was sleepy but as of the 4th I'm not sleepy during the days anymore. I have 2 thoughts: 1. I have a sensitivity to one of the ingredients in the vaccine. 2. Although my symptoms are ever present they subside slightly as the day goes on and I'm convinced it's because I am taking in so many fluids on a daily basis to try and combat this thing. Any suggestions or thoughts on which ingredient has caused me so much angst are appreciated.
HISTORY: I have LPR but it doesn't present in this fashion and I haven't had problems from it in years.
ALLERGIES: Drugs that have made me sick in the past: Minocycline, Didocillin 500mg, Levaquin and intolerance for Silicone contacts.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my first Moderna vaccine shot on 03/24/2021. After about 15 min I felt light headed and had a ringing in my ears, both symptoms went away after about 15 - 20 min. I received my second dose on 04/21/2021, with no immediate side effects, or any noted side effects the rest of the day. The next morning I experienced fatigue and chills (no fever), and a ringing in my ears, I also had a metallic taste in my mouth. Two days after the second dose I felt a little fatigued, no chills, no metal taste, however the ringing in the ears was still present. The ringing in the ears was almost gone by the third day, however yesterday is became more intense and the metallic taste came back. The ringing subsided after about 20 - 30 mins but was still present and the metallic taste went away. As of this morning I still have a ringing in my ears and the metallic taste came back.  I have read online that all of these symptoms have been noted after receiving Covid vaccines. I don't feel particularly congested, aside from some stuffiness from being outdoors and mowing the lawn, etc. however in the past I have experienced a metallic taste accompanied with a sinus infection/allergies to fir tree pollen. However none of these symptoms were present prior to my second Moderna dose. I'm concerned about the ringing in my ears, it's very irritating and my concern is that it is still present fifteen days after I received my second Moderna dose.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Pt received the 1st COVID vaccine on 04/14/2021 (Pfizer, Lot #: EW0162 and expiration date: 08/31/2021) on his left arm at 1516 PM. Client presented to the vaccine site today, 05/05/2021, for his second dose appointment. As the vaccinator conducted a health screening, some medical concerns came up. As a result, the nurse was called over for a consult. Client expressed that the following day, he developed a sore arm. However, about 3- 4 days later the client also reported that he developed "chest pain" on his left side, under the nipple. Client stated that the pain was "for sure a muscle pain." Client denied any other symptoms. Client denied having any shortness of breath, trouble breathing, or any pain with breathing. Client expressed that it was about a 6- 7 on pain scale of 0 to 10 and lasted about 8- 9 days. Client also stated that he had trouble sleeping for the first 3- 4 days after the vaccine due to the chest pain but the client did not complete any interventions for the pain, he just monitored it and let the symptoms resolve on its own. When asked if he had done any physical activity or exercise around his first dose, patient disclosed that a few days before his first dose he did go to the beach and play ball. However, he did not recall injuring his left side. Patient has a history of gastritis and acid reflux. Patient is not currently taking any medications and has no known drug allergies. Patient stated he has seasonal allergies and will take Zyrtec, if needed. Patient also recalled that about 20 years ago, he received an injectable medication in the emergency department for a fall and bruising. The medication made him "vomit and paralyzed him for about 5 minutes." Client could not remember the name of the medication. Patient expresses a needle fear and stated he gets "anxious and dizzy around needles." First dose was given in the zero gravity chair. Patient did not follow- up with his primary care provider regarding the chest pain, but stated he is still concerned about it. Patient states that the chest pain has since resolved, has not come back, and he feels "good" today. At 1407, vital signs were taken by Medic while the client was sitting: blood pressure: 122/90, heart rate: 65, respiratory rate: 18, and skin was normal, dry, intact, and normal. Nurse consulted with the medical team and they advised that it was safe to proceed with the second dose with a 30 minute observation in the zero gravity chair. Nurse recommend that the client follow- up with his primary care provider and educated him on the use of V- safe. The 2nd COVID vaccine was given on 05/05/2021 (Pfizer, Lot #: EW0167 and expiration date: 08/31/2021) on his right arm at 1434 PM. Client walked out of the site with a steady gait after waiting 30 minutes in the observation area.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Covid-19 vaccine (Pfizer-Biotech) first dose (Lot # EW0161) was administered into the left deltoid on 4/19/2021 at 5:04 PM. The second dose was administered on 5/5/2021 at 5:15 PM or day 16.  The second dose was not administered with in the 4 day window and considered an "Administration Error."  Determination of how the error occurred and corrective strategies to prevent it from happening again were reinforced and implemented.  Patient came early as she thought she saw a pop-up window when she had registered for first dose stating that her second dose was May 5 and this is the date she put on her calendar. Patient received her first dose and second dose at a vaccination Center.  The actual e-mail she showed the staff and her CDC card both stated the correct date of May 10th. Thus, both registration and the vaccine floor did not correctly identify the date the second dose was to be administered.  Patient did not realize until after the second shot had been administered that her card actually said she was due May 10th.  She brought it to attention of the staff, post facto.    Corrective action included reminding registration, nursing, and data entry staff leads the following morning to be certain that each person verifies the vaccine is occurring within the 4-day window of the due date and not earlier.   Patient was discharged home following an uneventful observation.

Pt arrived to clinic for Covid-19 Vaccine, first dose. No hx of allergies to food, medicine, or vaccine. Hx of anxiety, no history medication management for anxiety.  Vaccine administered at approximately 1:20pm, pt advised to remain in clinic for routine monitoring for 15 min. RN reports pt appeared anxious prior to vaccine. 1:45 Pt denied signs and symptoms of allergic reaction after receiving Covid vaccine, and was allowed to exit clinic area. Pt left with steady gait, no distress reported.  1:49 Pt returned to clinic, c/o throat and tongue feeling warm, pt appeared anxious and pale. PT placed in seated position RN at pt side.  1:50 J. Staff at pts side. Vitals BP 170/110, HR 121, RR 26, 98% o2. EMS called by RN. Epi pen ready at pts side, no Epi administered at this time.  1:52 Pt continues to present pale, small cough noted, pt denies swelling to throat, reports warm sensation to tongue and throat, ?My tongue and throat feel different.? Noted redness to outer sclera bilaterally.  Speech clear. Sat 98% HR 117 2:10 Vitals: BP 180/100, HR 130, RR 26, 98%, pt pale, speech clear, pt remains alert and oriented. 2:13-EMS arrived, report given to EMS by Pharm, pt remains alert but pale, PT left clinic via gurney with EMS.

The patient received the vaccine. He tolerated it well. He denied previous vaccination for COVID, COVID 19 infection or known drug allergies. Upon entering the person into  I saw that he had been previously fully vaccinated with the Moderna vaccine completing his  second dose in April.

Administered vaccine at 0920. Patient got up, went to the bathroom then returned to seat. Around 0935 started feeling hot. Water bottle given to patient and cool cloth applied to neck. Patient began to feel dizzy. Encouraged patient to lean forward, resting head on arms and taking slow deep breaths. Patient states that leaning forward was not helping. Encouraged patient to lean forward further or gave option to lay down on ground. RN assisted patient to ground when patient stated that she was starting to feel tingling in her throat. Denies SOB. Called urgent care provider, in at 0936 to assess patient. Provider arrived to vaccination conference room at 0938 and assessed patient. Patient states she is having tingling in throat, denied having trouble breathing but then started to cough. Provider directed RN to give epipen injection of 0.3mg to patient. RN administered 0.3mg EpiPen to patient in her left lateral thigh at 0941. Provider informed patient that we would call EMS to bring her to the hospital. Vitals: O2 100%, pulse 79, BP 138/91. Provider stepped out of room to get additional supplies, RN remained with patient. Patient and husband agreed with plan. Patient then started to feel SOB, gasping for air and face became red.  RN alerted provider and had MA in room call EMS called @ 0943.  Provider back in room at 0944. At 0944, BP 148/99, pulse 116, O2 100%. 2L of oxygen applied via face mask per provider. At 0946, BP 142/92, pulse 112. Patient's face no longer bright red, breathing slowed at regular rate and patient closed her eyes. Patient less alert and denied trouble breathing states her throat still tingles, answers to commands with stimulation to rouse patient. At 0950 BP 129/80, pulse 90, O2 100%, patient is oriented x4, is following verbal commands states she is "just tired". At 0951, EMS arrived and assessed patient. Report given to medics and patient was transported to nearby hospital. Patient left via EMS at 1002.
ALLERGIES: Per husband, no hx of allergies

First of two vaccine injections received roughly 3-4 weeks ago. Onset of severe dyspnea on exertion 5 days ago. Echocardiogram demonstrates severe global hypokinesis with an estimated ejection fraction of 15%. No antecedent history of dyspnea, drug use, angina or heart disease. No prior physical limitations. Relation of new onset/newly diagnosed cardiomyopathy to vaccine is unknown. Investigation and clarification of particulars (including which vaccine, date of injection, etc.) to follow. This communication prompted by ECHO review.
LAB_DATA: Echocardiogram obtained morning of 5/5/21. Severe global hypokinesis with estimated ejection fraction 15%. Further testing will follow - admission planned.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Seizure: no signs, the duration of the seizure was short and lasted 10 seconds approximately, though I cannot be sure. I was conscious when the seizure happened though a bit out of it. I remember after using the bathroom I started to have a convulsion when I stood up and then I was on the ground on my stomach and my head was flopping and banging on the ground. Following the incident I had very sensitive to the touch soreness on both temples. After this happened I struggled to get up off the flow and back into bed. I remember crawling sloppily and pawing at the bed to try to get back into it, it was as though my body was not coordinated. I believe I feel asleep after that. Some time after I woke up on my back in the middle of the room with a very sore spot on the back of my head. I assume I blacked out and fell and hit my head, but I don?t remember. I had a headache afterward for several hours.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient was seated for 15 minutes following the vaccination and when he got up to retrieve his vaccination record card he passed out onto the floor. He was attended to by the nurse on staff as well as myself. Reported no pain, knew his name and where he was. Stated no history of seizures and was not diabetic. Stated he has not eaten today, only a Starbucks. We got him up to a chair after a few minutes and attempted to take his blood pressure. He passed out a second time and we got him to the floor. He was alert shortly after getting him to a laying position. Ambulance was called and he was taken to be checked out.  Patient did return the next day to thank us and let us know he had a CT and labs done. His physician thought it was a vasovagal episode. He is to follow up with his primary physician soon.

Covid shot Feb. 3,2021         Moderna                                                       Keep in mind I did not put all the pieces together until a month later. Very important to note my hands are very strong, like vise grips, so to wake up not being able to make a fist was very difficult, not to mention not being able to pull up my underwear. Feb 4,5,6,7 Redness on Left arm, no real aches or pains. Continued to work, wasn?t feeling so good, legs very tired. Left work early 2/11 and 12. Was out 2/18 left 1hr. early 2/19 Feb 18th went to see DR. complaining of muscle weakness and aches in my hands and legs. Stiffness in hands I thought was because of walking with the cane. Then left hand started hurting. Strangely keep burping for no reason. Noticed my pelvic floor  are weak. Just standing up and my bladder starts to leak. Frustrating..  I am dealing with Lymphedema in legs and bad knees, so all these aches and pains are common. Took the week of 2/22 to 2/26 off of work to relax, hoping to recover. Things got a little better when I got back in pool therapy. Went to see Ortho DR 2/24 he drained 65ml of fluid out of the left knee, and 45ml out of right knee. Got a Gel One injection both knees. No help. Went to see Ortho Dr. , who informed me that all has been done to help, time to replace knee. Feb. 27,28, Feeling better, started questioning Covid shot side effects after seeing an article on TV. Thursday 3/4 Dr  did not think my aches and pains were from the shot. So Only way to know for sure was to have second shot, March 6TH. 2nd shot March 6th All went well, redness on left arm Sunday. However Sunday night got the chills, then woke up sweating. Hands to the elbows stiff and could not touch the top of my head. Every muscle and joint aches. Knees and feet all swollen. Pain on right side of neck. Takes me over an hour to stretch and bend just to get out of bed. My feet are elevated all night. Lower them to stretch. Sometimes legs feel like their on fire?? 3/8 Monday aches and pains. Tuesday Major stiffness felt like passing out in the shower, went to the Pool. Therapist had me keep arms lowered in the water flexing and stretching to get fluid to move. Felt a little better, but weak. Still burping for no reason. Still pain on right side of neck. Tuesday and Wednesday night same thing happened, chills then sweating. Thursday in the pool was tough.  Chills and sweating again at night. Major stiffness Friday, Sat and Sunday mornings. All day burping and hands very stiff/cold. Used heating pad to loosen up hands. 3/15 Monday morning woken up with chills again, hands so stiff and legs throbbing, having a difficult time getting out of bed. Went to take a shower, thought I was going to pass out. Pain on left side of neck. Stiffness elbows to finger tips. 3/16 and 3/18 pool therapy giving some relief with stiffness in hands and legs.  3/19 to 3/22 woke up with stiffness in hands to elbows. Left arm where the injection shot was given felt like someone was snapping an elastic on my arm every couple of minutes. Finally got it to go away by putting heating pad on it every morning. I also put heat on stiff hands, that seems to work a little. But the burping still won?t stop, my stomach just keeps rolling no matter what I eat or drink. On days that I did not have pool therapy it would take 3 to 6 hrs to get hands to loosen up using heating pad. 3/23 went to pool therapy, had a tough time walking in/out. Legs feel like they can?t hold me up. Therapist had me work out again, trying to move the fluid out of my legs and arms/hands. By the time I got home hands were cold and stiff, feet feel tingly.. 3/23 Called primary care to discuss fluid in hands and legs, got the OK from both Dr?s to take fluid pill and also a Prednisone (4 days only) to flush my system. 3/24 to 3/26 still getting the chills and stiffness in hands, not a bad, finally going away?? Hopefully. 3/26 to 3/29 hands are finally loosening up, not as much stiffness, only takes couple of hrs. of get hands to function. This has been a very difficult recovery..  April 5th had my knee replaced, what ever medicine they gave me, my hands were not swollen at all 3 days then I went to Rehab and the swelling started all over again. Today is May 6th and the hands are still cold and slightly stiff. The stomach is still burping. Pelvic floor getting better. Only asking if you heard of this and if you have a cure? Need my blood to Test? Would like to have my life back to normal. Thank you,

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Client received her second dose of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine (Lot #EW0179 Exp. 8/2021) at 10:03 AM. EMT saw client stand in observation area. Client appeared "unsteady on her feet". EMT rushed to patient and guided her slowly to the ground while protecting her head. Patient then fainted. EMTs assisted patient to gravity bed where patient regained consciousness. Patient was alert and oriented to person, place, time, and event (AAO x 4) immediately following the incident. Client's vitals were assessed every 5 minutes. They were recorded as follows 10:19- Blood Pressure (BP) 100/74, Heart Rate (HR) 86, Oxygen Saturation (SPO2) 99%, and Respiratory Rate (RR) 18; 10:24- BP 100/72, HR 81, SPO2 99% RR 18; 10:29- BP 100/76, HR 82, SPO2 99% RR 16; 10:34- BP 102/74, HR 84, SPO2 99% RR 18; 10:39- BP 100/72, HR 82, SPO2 99% RR 18; 10:44- BP 110/76, HR 86, SPO2 99% RR 18. Client was given a bottle of water and instructed to remain in a semi-fowler's (45 degree) position until vitals stabilized. Patient remained on vaccination site for 30 minutes following the episode of fainting. EMT obtained orthostatic vital signs (vital trend from lying down, to sitting, to standing). Patient was negative for orthostatic hypotension. Symptoms resolved as indicated above in vital signs. Patient stated she was "feeling better" and declined EMS transport. Patient and father were educated by RN on home care (rest and fluids) and to seek emergency medical attention if symptoms persisted or worsened. Patient left the vaccination site at 10:45 with father and sister with steady gait and in no change in status.
ALLERGIES: History of anaphylactic reaction to bananas

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient is a 74 y/o female with PMH significant for meningitis at age 2 resulting in developmental delay (non-verbal at baseline and seizure disorder) who presented for poor oral intake, dysphagia, and inability walk due to increased lower extremity weakness that has been occurring since April 9th. The patient is typically ambulatory but needs significant assistance with ADLs. She is able to feed herself (tends to eat baby food). Eventually, the patient was admitted for sepsis 2/2 UTI and now with concerns for remote stroke with persistent dysphagia and acute encephalopathy.   Since April 9th, the family has noted that the patient has had difficulty swallowing baby food and seems to be uncomfortable; she is able to make a couple of audible sounds or gestures that suggest pain and that is why they brought her. The family also reports that the patient received her second dose of the Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 vaccine on 04/07/2021.   On 04/08/2021, the patient had one staring episode, but then returned to baseline. She was at baseline during breakfast on the morning on 04/09/2021, but around lunchtime, she had another staring spell and was unable to swallow food as well as unable to walk, stand, or move her lower extremities. The patient has limited language at baseline but also has not been able to say the few words she used to communicate with her family, only moaning and grunting since that time. Since 04/09, she has not been able to consume any solid foods, only eating a very small amount of smashed/liquified fruit and drinking Pedialyte. Sister has been massaging her legs regularly in hopes of re-establishing movement but saw nothing until yesterday (05/05/2021) when the patient moved toes bilaterally and briefly lifted her right leg.    Neurology Consult on 05/05/2021:  The patient had mildly bradycardiac and hypertensive (170s/80s). Labs reviewed and showed mildly elevated WBC (i.e., 12.9 K/MM3) and urinalysis was consistent with UTI.  Imaging was reviewed and consistent with chronic CVA, likely occurring on 04/09/2021 while the patient was in hypercoagulable post-COVID vaccine state.   Neurology recommends CT angio head and neck, TTE w/ bubble, A1c, fasting lipid panel, DVT prophylaxis via lovenox 40mg SC daily, D-dimer levels, EKG, PT/OT?Speech therapy evals, BP control via lisinopril 10mg daily w/ goal of < 140/90, and ASA 81mg daily
LAB_DATA: Imaging on 05/06/2021:  CT and MRI Impression: Ill-defined focus of restricted diffusion with blood products, FLAIR hyperintensity, and patchy heterogenous enhancement in the posterior right frontal lobe. This is favored to represent an evolving infarct with hemorrhagic-conversion and blood brain barrier breakdown with contrast leakage. Asymmetric atrophy of the left cerebral hemisphere relative to the right with increased FLAIR/T2 hyperintensity. This is nonspecific and may be due to tosequela of a remote cerebral insult such as encephalitis or a remote vascular insult.   Labs 05/06/2021:  D-Dimer level: 1034  Troponin-T, high sensitivity: 17
OTHER_MEDS: Phenytoin 125 mg/5mL oral suspension, 250mg = 10mL, oral, BID   Primidone 250mg PO BID
CUR_ILL: Sepsis secondary to UTI with WBC of 12 (leukocytosis), HR > 90, and urine culture positive for pseudomonas as the primary source of infection.   The patient also displays hypokalemia with concern for refeeding syndrome due to low oral intake as well as an anion gap metabolic acidosis (AGMA), potentially due to starvation ketoacidosis.
HISTORY: PMH significant for meningitis at age 2 resulting in developmental delay (non-verbal at baseline and seizure disorder)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 0 hours after injection: immediate soreness at injection site but mild - no treatment sought. 6 hours after injection: noticable ringing in left ear and pressure in left ear similar to what I normally experience with a head cold - no treatment sought. 10 hours after injection: soreness at injection site increasing, pressure in ear increasing, mild headache developed - orally took 10 mg of melatonin to try to sleep through the discomfort/pain. 12.5 hours after injection: awoke due to severe arm pain and feeling that I was going to throw up. Also felt like I had a fever due to feeling very hot followed by chills, but did not take my temperature.  My headache worsened and felt like when I get a migraine (I usually have about 1 migraine a year).  I also had mild muscle aches all over my body.  I took 800 mg of ibuprofen and propped myself upright with a trashcan next to me. 13.5 hours after injection: called out of work for the following day and shortly after fell back asleep.  I did not throw up. 16.5 hours after injection: woke up with reduced soreness at injection site, reduced headache, reduced nausea, increased fatigue. - Fell back asleep. 21.5 hours after injection: woke up with moderate soreness at injection site, increased headache, no body aches, and overwhelming fatigue - took another 800 mg of ibuprofen  and 10 mg Phenylephrine (and regular daily medication: 40 mg Adderall XR, 75 mg Venlafaxine HCl, 10 mg Loratadine, 0.5 mg Benztropine mesylate, 5 mg Midodrine HCl, centrum multivitamin, and Yaz birth control) 23.5 hours after injection: decreased soreness at injection site, no headache, extreme exhaustion, and moderate upset stomach making it difficult to eat. - ate a couple bites of rice and drank water and then fell back asleep. 25.5 hours after injection: woke up  with mild pain at injection site, mild headache (front of head, similar to a sinus headache), ringing and pressure in left ear has decreased but still noticable, moderate fatigue, difficulty focusing.
OTHER_MEDS: Adderall XR, Adderall, Effexor XR, Loratadine, Midodrine, Benztropine mesylate, Centrum adult multivitamin
HISTORY: ADD, Vasodepressor syncope, bipolar depression type 2, seasonal allergies

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On 5/4/21, patient came to get a 2nd dose Moderna vaccine. Vaccinating pharmacist verified patient information and asked some questions about his previous dose. Patient answered he just had sore arm and didn't have any other discomfort. After giving the vaccine, as I was trying to sign patient's vaccination card, I noticed he got Pfizer vaccine as a first dose in Nevada. I told him what he just got is Moderna. Then the patient said that's what he told my technician at the window when he was checking in.  My technician later denied the fact him ever mentioning about Pfizer. Patient did put it on the consent form that his first dose was Pfizer in Nevada. He told me he was already 2 weeks behind from getting his second Pfizer vaccine and he has been frustrated because he had been rescheduled twice. Turns out, he went to another medical center the same day (5/4/21) but then he couldn't get it there. It seems like the he made two appointments, one at the other medical center and one with us, and after being turned down from the other place he came to us. I told the patient that he might need to get a booster of Moderna again in 4 weeks and he was okay with it. Later that day, I called Moderna and CDC and found out he does not need to get another booster of Moderna because he got 2 doses of mRNA vaccines, but since the safety and efficacy is not studied about mixing 2 different mRNA vaccine yet, this is considered a vaccination error. I called patient today 5/6/21 and let him know that he doesn't need another dose of Moderna and he is fully vaccinated. He doesn't have a primary care provider and doesn't have any adverse reaction or discomfort other than sore arm as of 5/6/21.

From Physician H&P:  Patient is a 59-year-old man multiple medical chronic conditions, including known protein S deficiency not on anticoagulation, sinus bradycardia, hypercholesterolemia, chronic neuropathy of the lower extremities, who presented to the emergency room at the recommendation of his primary care office for possible stroke and persistent headache. He reports that his history of present illness begins on 4/7/2021, for which after he had received the COVID-19 Johnson & Johnson vaccine he started to have throbbing headache. He stated that it was diffuse and pounding in quality, up to 10 out of 10 pain. However this resolved on its own, and since then and has been intermittent with this type of headache. He did report 2 weeks ago, that he had a brief episode of tunnel vision as he describes it, where his vision seemed to narrow while he was looking at his phone. This only lasted no more than 10-30 minutes, and this resolved on its own as well. He continues to have intermittent headaches, again otherwise nonspecific with pounding quality however the intensity is improved. Humidifier regarding the Johnson & Johnson vaccine to report any side effects, for which she had notified his primary care doctor who then decided to proceed with MRI of the brain to evaluate for possible etiology. The MRI was done with and without contrast at facility on 5/4/2021, for which there was concern for possible left temporal posterior stroke, and if there was any concern for venous thrombosis, further imaging was necessary. He was then recommended to go to the emergency room for evaluation. He otherwise is in his regular state of health. He denies any recent fever or chills or cough, no chest pain or shortness of breath, nausea, vomiting, abdominal pain. No changes in bowel or bladder habits.
LAB_DATA: Brain MRI:  Small area of cortical enhancement involving the left posterior temporal lobe/occipital lobe. No associated restricted diffusion to suggest acute ischemia. Findings may be infectious, inflammatory, or secondary to recent ischemia. Correlate with prior imaging.

Patient presented to ED with chest tightness on 4/20/21  54YO male with PMH significant for CAD s/p PCI to RCA x2 (2003, 2005), chronic HBV, GI bleed, H. pylori gastritis presented to the hospital with chest tightness. Patient had just finished working out for about 45 minutes when he noted tightness across his lower chest/epigastric region. Found to be in V tach upon arrival and underwent electrical cardioversion with relief of symptoms. Patient was aspirin loaded and started on heparin and lidocaine drips. He underwent cardiac cath which did not show any hemodynamically significant stenosis. Also underwent cardiac MRI which demonstrated a non-viable transmural infarct of the inferior wall. Etiology of VT was thought to be scar mediated from prior MI. Patient underwent uncomplicated ICD placement and was started on metoprolol. ICD interrogation POD 1 was unremarkable. Patient discharged in stable condition with close follow up with PCP, Cardiology, and EP. Patient with unchanged coronaries and unchanged ejection fraction. Patient received Covid-19 Pfizer vaccine IM on 3/27 (left deltioid - LOT ER8733) and 4/17 (left deltioid - LOT EW0170).
LAB_DATA: Cardiac MRI (4/21/21)Transmural late gadolinium enhancement of the inferior and inferoseptal walls of the basal segment with extension into the inferior wall of the mid cavity along with associated thinning and hypokinesis/akinesis are consistent with non-viable transmural infarct. Left ventricular dilatation and decreased left ventricular systolic function. Left ventricular ejection fraction is 37%. The calculated right ventricular ejection fraction is 36%. No pericardial enhancement.No significant valvular dysfunction.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Description of incident: Following administration of second COVID-19 vaccine, patient was sitting in the observation area for his 15 minute watch time. Blood pressure taken at 1435 and blood pressure was found to be 61/38 with a map of 45, taken on the right upper arm. Patient was immediately placed in the recliner and reclined with legs elevated. Per vaccinating RN, the patient was alert and oriented and speaking clearly when vaccine was administered. Initial Vitals at 1435. Blood pressure:  61/38 map 45 on right upper extremity with adult regular cuff. Pulse: 66; Respirations: 18; O2 saturation: 74% on room air. Patient placed on 15 liters of oxygen via non-rebreather mask. EMS called at 1437. Vital signs at 1438. Blood pressure: 96/56 map 69 on right upper arm with adult cuff. Pulse: 62; Respirations: 18; O2 saturation: 100% on non-rebreather. Clinical response team called, NP at side of recliner assessing patient. Vitals at 1440: Blood pressure: 104/61 right upper extremity with adult cuff. Pulse: 61; Respirations: 18; O2 saturations: 100% on 15 L non-rebreather mask. Vitals at 1442: Blood pressure: 104/59 map 74; Pulse: 59; Respirations: 18; O2 saturations: 100% on non-rebreather mask. EMS arrived to the triage room at 1446. Vitals at 1448: Blood pressure: 107/60 map of 76. On adult cuff right upper extremity. Pulse: 64; Respirations: 18; O2 saturations: 100% on non-rebreather mask. Blood glucose taken: 111. Orders initiated per RN protocol: None, protocol not warranted. Oxygen placed on patient via non-rebreather mask. Patient not wanting to go to the hospital, patient's daughter is on the phone trying to convince him to go to the hospital to be checked out. Patient stating "I just really want to go home." Patient's wife is here as well trying to convince him to go to the hospital. Patient attached to EMS monitors upon arrival at 1446. Vital signs at 1510: Blood pressure 153/80 map 108 on right upper extremity, adult regular cuff. Heart rate: 69; Respiratory rate: 18; O2 saturation level: 99% on room air. Vitals signs sitting at 1516: Blood pressure: adult regular cuff RUE 134/76 map 95; Heart rate: 76. Respirations: 18; O2 saturations: 99% on room air. Vital signs standing: Blood pressure: 156/79 map 104 adult regular cuff on RUE. Heart rate: 76; Respirations: 18; O2 saturations:99% on room air. Patient's daughter, here now at 1520 and speaking with patient and convincing him to go the hospital to be checked out. Patient now at 1531 agreeing to go to the hospital. Patient able to stand and transfer himself to the ambulance gurney. Patient outcome:  Patient transferred via EMS to Hospital at 1534. Patient left vaccine clinic via ambulance at 1534.

Patient reports that she takes Hydroxyzine for anxiety in emergencies. She also takes Zoloft for depression. Patient denies any history of diabetes and heart conditions. Patient reports that she has an inhaler that she has not used recently. She reports she uses it for "when she overheats". Patient denies chest or throat tightness. Presented patient to NP. Agreed with plan for patient to wait in observation station until patient felt comfortable returning home. Coached patient in deep breathing exercises and advised patient on signs of more severe reactions and when to be seen at an Emergency room. Patient agreed to plan and verbalized a second time that she had no chest or throat tightness. Patient left at 2:02pm.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Two hours after receiving the first doze, I started to get dizzy (the room started to spin). I contacted the pharmacy to ask if it was a common side effect, and the pharmacist told me to lie down on my side to see if the dizziness goes away in about 30 minutes. It didn't. I contacted the office of my primary care physician, and the nurse told me that it was not a common side effect, that I should go into the urgent care or ER. I did not take myself in, as I was feeling extremely dizzy. After 8 hours from getting the shot, I started to feel better and went to sleep. I felt better the next morning; however, I continued to have on and off dizziness/vertigo for the next 10 days, to the point that I chose not to drive my children around. In addition to dizziness/vertigo, during the first 10 days, I also experienced sensitivity to sounds and a feeling of a band around my head, squeezing. From day 11 to day 14, I experienced extreme fatigue. I was out of breath and my heart was racing from doing basic activities, such as cooking, cleaning the floor, and walking from one room to another.
LAB_DATA: I visited my primary care physician on 4/21. He checked my vitals and everything was normal. He mentioned that dizziness is a common side effect of the vaccine being reported.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient experienced sudden dizziness and nausea within 5 minutes of receiving Janssen COVID-19 immunization. Gave her water, crackers and cold/wet rags for her forehead as she felt hot. Took her temperature, returned normal. Gave her a trash can to keep near. Kept an eye on the patient and realized she was getting red in the face and more dizzy than she had been. Went out and stood next to patient, with her mom on her other side. Began to experience light sensitivity, feeling like the room was spinning. Patient almost fell out of the chair while sitting still. Mom used a personal pulse oximeter on patient, all results normal. Asked the patient about other symptoms, such as chest/abdominal/leg pain, headache, shortness of breath. Patient reported a headache, dizziness, nausea and leg numbness roughly 30 minutes following the vaccine. I recommended going to the ER, mom believed it would pass with time, but insisted she never responds this way to immunizations. Patient began to experience stabbing chest and abdominal pain around 45 minutes. Patient's mom was still hesitant to take her to the ER immediately on her own and asked us to call her PCP. He wanted the patient to go to the ER. Patient believed she would fall if she stood, offered to get a motorized cart, wheelchair or call an ambulance to transport her. Both patient and mom requested the ambulance. Asked a technician to check patient medications and allergies for EMTs, retook the patient's temperature which was normal again. Stayed with patient until EMTs arrived, reported all symptoms patient was experiencing.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient presented to her PCP office on 04/20 reporting that on 04/16 she received her 2nd Pfizer vaccine and the following day on 04/17 she started feeling muscle aches, fatigue and R calf pain from high ankle to the back of knee. On 04/18, all symptoms except the calf pain resolved. She continued to have 1-2/10  calf pain w/o skin changes but mild R > L enlargement of the lower leg. Reported a 3 hour car ride on 04/18 after the calf pain had already started. Denied chest pain, shortness of breath or palpitations. On exam, vital signs stable, right lower leg diffusely tender to palpation and noted to be 4 cm larger in circumference than the left side.  Patient was sent for an urgent outpatient duplex ultrasound of her right lower extremity. Ultrasound showed distal DVT in right peroneal veins. She was immediately instructed to discontinue the use of the Nuva ring and started on Xarelto 15 mg BID, with good symptom improvement. Was followed up in clinic on 05/05 with plan to transition to the Xarelto 20 mg QD on 05/13 for a total of 3 months of anticoagulation.
LAB_DATA: Right lower extremity duplex ultrasound on 04/20
OTHER_MEDS: Nuva ring Prozac 20mg daily Pmecrolimus cream 1% as needed

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Chills, low grade fever 96.5, bad body pain, sleepy, thirsty. headache.  Lasted all day Saturday 4-10-21. Sunday 4-11-21 no energy, tired. My right arm had a large pink shadow on my skin, arm was sore for 3 days. By  Monday 4-12-21 I was ok.  1 week later had a pea size nodule under my  right arm.  It was sore.  It went away after 2 days.

hives on arms, chest, face including mouth which are very itchy

Approx. 15 minutes post injection. Increased pulse rate of 120, chest pains, slight difficulty breathing, very shaky and lightheaded.  Not short of breath, he was able to have meaningful conversation. He appeared in pain. He did indicate an history of stress induced seizure.

4 days after receiving the vaccine, I woke up with slight pins and needles sensation; and some numbness in my thumb, index finger and middle finger of my right hand. These sensations gradually increased. Worked Sunday and Monday. On Tuesday, I woke up with those symptoms plus pain in those fingers and an intense burning pain at the base of my right palm. After ibuprofen, it improved some. Went to work. As I was working, pins and needles sensation started in left pinkie finger, ring finger and pinkie finger of right hand. I was advised to go seek medical care. After an assessment, I was told it was carpal tunnel. I have had no prior history of this and I've never experienced these symptoms before. I was given a brace for each wrist.
Accidental needlestick after administering  to patient. After vaccinating the patient, I went to put the safety clip on and accidentally pricked my thumb.
LAB_DATA: I went to have bloodwork done for HIV and hepatitis

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Started to get tired and thirsty the evening of the 30th a few hours after the vaccine. Went to bed around 10:30 and woke up about 3 hours later at 1:30. Had chills and was shaking when I got up. Could not really fall back asleep. Chills turned into a fever. That morning I started to get a headache. I sounded congested at one point, but no runny nose. I also had body and joint aches.  I took Excedrin three times that day. Once in the morning, once in the afternoon, once before bed. I used zquil to sleep a little bit in the afternoon and again at night. I woke up Sunday and felt completely fine except for my arm still being sore.

I had stayed awake because I work nights and then I went to sleep. I woke up with excruciating headache - worst I've ever had. I checked my temperature - it was 99.4 and I had chills. I normally run cold.  I felt awful I took a couple of Tylenol and ibuprofen - waited for it to take the bite off so I could go to sleep. I called off into work. I waited until about 11:00 - 11:30 enough so I could go back to sleep. I took two more Tylenol and Ibuprofen and I took Benadryl. I woke up the next day and felt great when I woke up. Sometime in early-mid March, I had a flare up of pain. First it was my hands - from my elbows down to my fingertips - started to hurt. My hands were aching. It started spreading throughout my whole body - hands, knees, ankles, back - it was moving. One day, I couldn't even move. I was taking Ibuprofen non-stop, I was in so much pain. My hands were hot and throbbing like I was sunburnt. My knuckles and joints were aching - everything was swelling up. Mostly staying in the joints - felt hot and achy. I slept with ice on my hands. At work, I kept filling up plastic bags with ice and holding them on my hands. Symptoms were from neck to tailbone  - my whole spine - and my hips. Sometimes it was all the above - everything below my ears along with a very mild headache. And then it became focused in certain spots. It shifts up and down. It definitely stays in my sacral region and my greater trochanter in my hips; in my elbows and in my knees. It is now starting to get a bit better -  it's nothing like it was before.  It took awhile to reach my Primary Dr. to get a  referral for Rheumatologist. Had gone to Urgent Care on  April 7, 2021; Doctor visit 4/29/2021
LAB_DATA: April 19, 2021 - I had RF - negative  and CRP done by the clinic. RF - negative; CRP moderately elevated - 1.6  - high -
OTHER_MEDS: Zoloft; Ramipril; Chlorthalidone; Zetia; Crestor; Folic Acid; Omega 3; Vit D3 - 5000 IU; Provigil;  Tylenol or Ibuprofen when I have pain.
HISTORY: Hyper-tension; high cholesterol; obesity; migraines with aura; I had mono when I was 16; depression; Osteo-arthritis; trying to see if I have RA at the current time

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On the 2nd night after receiving the 1st shot of Moderna vaccine, I experienced intense abdominal pain. It was like if someone was pulling and twisting my intestines. The pain was acute  for about 1hr, then it started fading with renewed but shorter periods of more intense pain. I thought of peritonitis, and if the pain didn't subside I might have called an ambulance. I just decided to lay low  and let the pain pass. It was scary.  The next day on May 3rd, I awoke with rush over my upper body,. Little bubbles was dispersed across my abdomen, shoulders, sides but were few and not dense, so I let it pass. Currently the rush is still on, thankfully don't have the abdominal pain any longer.  However, I am not sure that I shall get the 2nd Moderna shot. I won't survive the intestines twisting pain if increased.
LAB_DATA: Didn't go to see the doctor, my body is quite healthy and for 64 years stayed this way. I hope that my body could restore my gut and intestines to their healthy state. But again, I probably won't take again Moderna.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: A few days after receiving the first dose I started experiencing body aches, headache and minor back pain.  The body aches only continued to get worse over time as  well as the back pain. I did not have back problems or pain until the vaccine. I contacted my primary physician and explained that I received the vaccine and told her about my symptoms. She asked me to get a Covid-19 test. I did and the results was negative. At his point, May  6, 2021, the symptoms have only become worse. My back pain is so severe I can barely stand it. I have tried ice packs, a heating pad, over the counter pain medication and nothing has made it better. My physician does not know what to do. Another side effect is it has made my fibromyalgia pain much worse. I have had fibromyalgia for about fifteen years and my pain is tolerable but the past few weeks have been unbearable. I may have a weakened immune system due to the fibromyalgia so maybe  that could be a explanation for my symptoms. I wanted to know if other people have experienced severe side effects. The only treatment is over the counter pain medication and ice packs and a heating pad.  As of today, May 6, the back pain and body aches are still present and I would say severe. The headache is tolerable but still lingers and does not go away. The body aches, headache and back pain is twenty four hours a day and never get better.

First dose / in July 2018 / unaware until now that there is a second dose; This case was reported by a consumer via call center representative and described the occurrence of incomplete course of vaccination in a 74-year-old female patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) for prophylaxis.   Previously administered products included Shingrix (received 1st dose of Shingrix in July 2018 in left deltoid) and Zostavax (received Zostavax in 2014).   On an unknown date, the patient received the 2nd dose of Shingrix. On an unknown date, unknown after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced incomplete course of vaccination. On an unknown date, the outcome of the incomplete course of vaccination was unknown.  Additional information was provided as follows:  The reporter was the patient herself. The age at vaccination was not applicable for this report. Till the time of reporting, the patient did not receive 2nd dose of Shingrix, which led to incomplete course of vaccination. The reporter inquired about second dose of Shingrix vaccine.  The patient received her first dose of Shingrix in July 2018 at the pharmacy and was unaware until now that there is a second dose of Shingrix that needs to be administered to complete the series.  The patient stated that, she was neither informed by doctor nor the pharmacist about the second dose of the vaccine to complete the series.  The patient really would not like to get shingles, it was terrible. The patient inquired whether she should restart the series, because it has been almost 3 years since the first dose.  The patient did not know the dose or an exact date of administration, she only remembers that it was given in July 2018 and mentioned that, it might have been given in left arm in the upper region (deltoid), she always get vaccine in her non-dominant arm so it would have been left arm." The patient did not have a doctor's fax number.  The patient stated that she received Zostavax in 2014 and then couple years later she read about Shingrix at the pharmacy and they said it was recommended to get Shingrix even if you had Zostavax before, so patient  said why not, the patient did not want to want to get shingles.  The patient also mentioned that she received a complete series of COVID vaccine (Moderna) in February 2021 (first dose in January 2021 and second dose in February 2021).  The reporter provided a consent to follow up with HCP.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Bell's Palsy; lethargic; This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer (subsequently medically confirmed) and describes the occurrence of BELL'S PALSY (Bell's Palsy) in a 51-year-old male patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 025a21a) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below.     No Medical History information was reported.    On 06-Mar-2021 at 11:30 AM, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 07-Mar-2021, the patient experienced LETHARGY (lethargic). On 07-Mar-2021 at 12:00 PM, the patient experienced BELL'S PALSY (Bell's Palsy) (seriousness criterion medically significant). On 08-Mar-2021, LETHARGY (lethargic) had resolved. At the time of the report, BELL'S PALSY (Bell's Palsy) had not resolved.        The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown.       Patient began to experience paralysis of the facial muscles on the left side of his face along with lethargy that lasted one day. He was unable to blink his left eye and the left half of his tongue had no taste. He also reported blurry vision.  He subsequently called 911 and was diagnosed with Bell's Palsy in the emergency room that evening. That week, the left side of his face was drooping. He reported that it had tightened up and was more symmetrical now, however, he was still unable to smile, frown or blink from the left side of his face. He was scheduled to receive his second dose of the vaccine on 06-Apr-2021, however, his neurologist stated that she could not guarantee that it would not make his Bell's Palsy worse, but she still recommended getting the second dose. The medical staff at the base didn't know if he should get the second dose and his civilian doctor wouldn't commit. The emergency room physician contacted an Infectious Disease doctor who felt it would be fine for him to get the second dose.  Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter. No treatment information was provided. At day 13 I began to have upper thigh pain in my left leg and began to feel winded as I was would walk up steps and do housework which had not happened previously ever..  On 4/14/21 I requested an appointment with my primary care doctor, however he was booked for 2 weeks and I was referred to an associated PA  where I received a virtual consult. He only ran bloodwork, and in fact never even called me back on the bloodwork, and just posted it in the online profile. I now need to find a doctor that will run diagnostics and respect my concerns

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On day three after my Covid vaccine, after experiencing mostly mild side effects for the first two days, I experienced a severe episode of tachycardia while walking uphill. This is a walk I do three times a week and have never felt this way before. I couldn't catch my breath, and my heart rate remained abnormally elevated for another fifteen minutes. I walked down the hill and spoke to my doctor, who said it was likely a vaccine side effect and I should rest for the day. I continued to experience episodes of tachycardia, with heart rate in the 130s, throughout the rest of the day. I was short of breath just walking to the bathroom. My doctor had me come in and performed an EKG, which was normal. I continued having these symptoms the rest of the day, until eventually my heart rate stabilized  after 9pm. The next day I felt very tired, but no longer experienced the tachycardia. I had a follow up at my clinic and another normal EKG. Then yesterday evening, which was day 5 after the vaccine (technically day 6 maybe), I was walking my dog on a flat surface, taking my time, and I became short of breath, with pressure and tightness in my chest. I was unable to get a deep breath for another 30 minutes. Today, day 6/7 after my vaccine, I am fatigued, and continue to feel pressure and tightness in my chest throughout the day. I have asthma, and this feels different, though I have been using my inhaler to try to open up the tightness I'm experiencing. I also continue to have stomach pain and diarrhea since day one after receiving the vaccine. I also had that with the first vaccine three weeks ago--stomach pain and diarrhea.
LAB_DATA: EKGs on 5/3/21 and 5/4/21. Normal labs and abdominal ultrasound at the ER on 4/19/21, after my first dose of Pfizer.
OTHER_MEDS: Albuterol inhaler as needed, Flovent inhaler twice daily, multi-vitamin

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my second vaccination Tuesday around 5:30pm. I had a lower back muscle spasm on Monday morning, but the muscles were feeling significantly better by the time of my vaccination. I again took two ibuprofen before bed Tuesday night to help with my lower back muscles relax. (After I took the medicine, I then read that you aren?t supposed to take ibuprofen after the vaccine - the pharmacy unfortunately had only told me not to take Motrin - regardless the only other medicine I took was one Tylenol Wednesday morning). Wednesday morning I woke up with extreme back pain. This was in fact the worst lower back pain I?ve ever experienced. That lasted for about four hours. After that, my back pain subsided and I felt fine from around lunchtime until about 3. At that point I started to feel muscle aches throughout my body but especially in my legs. Around 6pm I started to get severe chills for the next three hours, although I never registered a fever I was shivering  at times. By 9pm I started to feel quite warm. I went to bed at 10pm still feeling a bit warm but was able to fall asleep. At 1am (Thursday) I woke up suddenly and was wide awake for the next two hours.  I still felt a bit warm and my muscle aches were quite strong. At 3am I fell back asleep. I woke up at 9:30am in a pool of sweat. However, my muscle aches had subsided and temperature felt normal when I woke up, but I felt tired and had a headache. My tiredness went away by early afternoon on Thursday and my headache went away around 6pm on Thursday, after which I felt back to normal.

Patient was attended to immediately by pharmacist  - he responded immediately to my talking to him and touching his shoulders. Patient was guided to an upright seated position, then helped to floor and asked to lie on floor with legs elevated. 911 was called and Seattle Fire Dept arrived about 5min later. Patient was fully aware of surroundings, his name, etc. Evaluated him and took multiple blood pressure readings with him laying on floor and eventually sitting up. His pressure was initially low but recovered to normal over 15-30 minutes. Ambulance was called but patient declined as his parents were on their way. Patient's blood pressure recovered to normal and he was able to sit and stand, was fully conversational throughout the episode. Patient left building of his own accord with his family to seek medical follow-up.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Throat and tongue swelling; Throat and tongue swelling; Heart break; Rapid breathing; Fluish; Arm is a bit sore; This spontaneous case was received on 12-Oct-2020 from other non-health professional (consumer)(reference number: SEQW20-03435) and concerned a 59-year-old, female patient.  The patient's historical vaccine included flu shot after which the patient was a bit fluish and arm was a bit sore. The patient's relevant medical history included diabetes type 2, psoriatic arthritis, hypothyroid, hypogammaglobulinemia and allergies to medicines who have preservatives. The patient's concomitant medications included Synthroid (levothyroxine sodium), Advair (fluticasone propionate, salmeterol xinafoate), Singular (montelukast sodium) and Levemir (insulin detemir), for an unknown indication.  On 14-Sep-2020, the patient was vaccinated with Flucelvax QIV (influenza vaccine, subunit influenza virus vaccine polyvalent; dose: 0.5 ml, anatomical location: left arm, and route of administration: intramuscular) for influenza prophylaxis. The batch number was not reported.  On the same day, 3/4 hours after receiving Flucelvax QIV, the patient's throat and tongue started swelling. The patient also experienced rapid breathing and heart break. Within one hour the symptoms started vanishing and in 2/3 hours the reaction was gone. The patient didn't need to use her Epipen (epinephrine). The patient was a bit "fluish" and her arm was a bit sore like never before.  On the same day, the patient recovered from all events.  The reporter did not provide a causality assessment to Flucelvax QIV.  The event of 'throat swelling', swelling of tongue', 'heart disorder' and 'tachypnea' were considered to be medically significant by a Physician within Seqirus's Pharmacovigilance and Risk Management Department.  This case is linked with case 202005140, due to the same patient.  Company comment: A female patient, was vaccinated with Flucelvax QIV vaccine. On the same day, 3/4 hours after receiving vaccine, the patient developed pharyngeal swelling, tongue swelling, tachypnoea and cardiac disorder. The patient also developed pain in extremity and influenza like-illness (was a bit "fluish").
